  <notes>
    Completed 2026-07-01 (~45 min, under 2 h estimate).

    Delivered:
      - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Compose/IDocxTextExtractor.cs` (interface;
        ADR-010 justified I/O-boundary seam so higher-level integration tests can mock
        without binding to WordprocessingDocument parse behavior).
      - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Compose/DocxTextExtractor.cs` (default impl):
          * Opens WordprocessingDocument read-only from the incoming Stream
          * Materializes paragraph text lists once (single OpenXml tree walk)
          * Concatenates paragraphs with `\n` separator
          * Truncates at maxCharacters with suffix ` [TRUNCATED — {N} characters more]`
            where N sums truncated-paragraph residue + remaining paragraphs' chars
            + paragraph-break newlines (accurate residue for prompt-budget telemetry)
          * Normalizes malformed input exceptions to `InvalidDataException` per the
            interface contract
          * Propagates CancellationToken at entry + between paragraph reads
      - `Infrastructure/DI/ComposeModule.cs` — UNCONDITIONAL Scoped registration per §F.1
        (matches unconditional endpoint mapping).
      - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/DocxTextExtractorTests.cs`:
        9 behavioral tests using in-memory DOCX fixtures (no binary files checked in;
        every scenario transparent in the test source):
          1. WithEmptyDocx_ReturnsEmptyString
          2. WithSimpleParagraphs_ConcatenatesWithParagraphBreaks
          3. WithMultipleRunsPerParagraph_ConcatenatesInDocumentOrder
             (Word split-run semantics: formatting-mid-paragraph splits into runs)
          4. WithHeadersAndFooters_SkipsThem
          5. WithCommentsPart_SkipsThem
          6. WhenTextExceedsMaxCharacters_TruncatesWithSuffix
             (verifies exact residue count: 21 remaining B's + newline + 50 C's = 72)
          7. WithMalformedDocxBytes_ThrowsInvalidDataException
          8. WithCancelledToken_ThrowsOperationCanceledException
          9. WithMaxCharactersLessThanOne_ThrowsArgumentOutOfRangeException

    Verification (all POML acceptance criteria):
      - #1 `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`: ✅ 0 errors / 19 warnings
        (all pre-existing; identical to baseline).
      - #2 `dotnet test ... --filter "FullyQualifiedName~DocxTextExtractor"`:
        ✅ **9/9 tests pass in 24 ms** (unit-domain KEEP category per ADR-038).
      - #3 Publish size: **45.47 MB compressed** (deploy/api-publish-t094.zip).
        Baseline post-W10 was **45.41 MB** — delta **+0.06 MB (~60 KB)** which is
        well under the < 0.5 MB POML target and the < 1 MB constraint. Confirms
        DocumentFormat.OpenXml 3.4.1 was already directly referenced in the .csproj
        (transitive presence + direct ref both verified); this task added no new
        binary payload beyond ~2 KB of our own .cs source.

    ADR-038 conformance:
      - Test category = `domain-logic` (unit-domain): the SUT is a pure function of
        its input stream. OpenXml is in-process; no HttpMessageHandler mocks (B1
        banned), no DI-registration tests (B3 banned), no ctor null-check tests
        (B4 banned), no mirror tests (B6 banned), no coverage-fillers (B10 banned).
      - Test path = `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Compose/**` — matches
        established BFF unit-test layout convention accepted by W9-071 audit and
        by the /test-diet report for R1.
      - Names conform to `{Method}_{Scenario}_{ExpectedResult}` (B13 compliance).
      - No `Stopwatch` / `DateTime.UtcNow` in tests (uses only cancellation +
        deterministic string content).

    Files touched (git status summary):
      - A `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Compose/IDocxTextExtractor.cs`
